ield=VIBE+%3D+volumetric+interpolated+breath-hold+examination&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">VIBE = volumetric interpolated breath-hold examination</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">MR imaging is an excellent tool for diagnosis and evaluation of various focal lesions and pathologic conditions of the spleen.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Khaled M.</span> <span property="familyName">Elsayes</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Mallinckrodt Institute of Radiology (K.M.E., V.R.N., G.M., C.O.M., J.P.H.) and Department of Surgical Pathology (J.S.L.), Washington University School of Medicine, 510 S Kingshighway Blvd, St Louis, MO 63110. Recipient of a Certificate of Merit award for an education exhibit at the 2003 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received July 30, 2004; revision requested September 23; revision received and accepted October 5. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Elsayes/Khaled+M" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Vamsidhar R.</span> <span property="familyName">Narra</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Mallinckrodt Institute of Radiology (K.M.E., V.R.N., G.M., C.O.M., J.P.H.) and Department of Surgical Pathology (J.S.L.), Washington Univer